    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "dSSWSHc8UiW5"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Exercise 7 ·** Select only `species`, `bill_length_mm`, `bill_depth_mm`,  \n",
        "`flipper_length_mm`, and `body_mass_g` from `penguins`.  \n",
        "Pivot to *long* format so you have columns `species`, `measurement`, `value`.  \n",
        "Then compute mean and standard deviation of each measurement per species.\n"
      ],
      "id": "dSSWSHc8UiW5"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "n_D6z6diUiW5"
      },
      "source": [
        "<details>\n",
        "<summary>💡 <b>Hint</b> (click to expand)</summary>\n",
        "\n",
        "```r\n",
        "penguins |>\n",
        "  select(species, bill_length_mm:body_mass_g) |>\n",
        "  pivot_longer(-species, names_to = \"measurement\", values_to = \"value\") |>\n",
        "  group_by(species, measurement) |>\n",
        "  summarise(mean = mean(value, na.rm=TRUE), sd = sd(value, na.rm=TRUE))\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "</details>"
      ],
      "id": "n_D6z6diUiW5"
    },
